parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall or shut off while in motion, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or stalls while riding
often at low speeds or when coming to a stop
the instrument panel may malfunction or not work
the bike may not start
and the engine may idle at high RPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Current Flow to Ignition Switch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive current flow to the ignition switch can cause the switch to fail, leading to ignition system failure and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails
causing the engine to shut off or stall
the instrument panel may malfunction or not work
and the bike may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ECU programming issues can cause the engine to idle at high RPM, leading to poor engine performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine idles at high RPM
often between 1300-2000 RPM
and there is no engine braking available.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Noise and Rattling (Timing Chain, Sprockets, and Tensioner Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain, sprockets, and tensioner can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine noise or rattling
vibration
loss of power
engine stalling
and in some cases
the rear tire may become slippery due to oil loss.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the output shaft bearing can cause the engine to lose oil, the rear tire to become slippery, and the upper shaft to create a hole in the engine, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loss of oil
rear tire becoming slippery
and the upper shaft creating a hole in the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disconnection of the transmission linkage can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear or neutral, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle gets stuck in gear or neutral
unable to shift gears
and may experience sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the gearbox can cause the vehicle to jump out of gear or fail to shift properly, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps out of gear
fails to shift into the next gear
or produces unusual noises
such as a rattling or grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam chain can cause excessive engine noise, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine produces excessive noise
such as a rattling or clunking sound
and may experience a loss of power or acceleration.
